ECET260 - Lab4

TFT Interfacing with STM32F4Discovery or STM32F407G-DISC1

View on GitHub Download .zip Download .tar.gz

Use STM32CubeMx and AC6 SystemWorkbench to interface TFT displays to the STM32F4Discovery or STM32F407G-DISC1 boards.

Currently supports SSD1289, ILI9341, ILI9481 and SSD1963



Part1:

Goto https://github.com/ECET260/TFT

Highlight the URL address at the top and CNTRL-C




Make a bitbucket account.



Click on Sketch – Verify/Compile or click the checkmark icon. This compiles our program.



Import a repository




Click on the defaults and fork this repository




Change the top right drop down from GIT to HTTPS. CNTRL -C the repository info.



In System Workbench, click on Window – Show View – Other – Git – Git Repositories and click OK.



Click on Window – Show View – Other – Git – Git Staging and click OK.










Clone a Git repository and add the clone to this view





It should fill in the parts from you CNTRL -C. You will need to login to your bitbucket account.















We only have the master branch.


Pick a local destination.

















You should now have a cloned repository in your file system.


File – Import - Existing Projects Into Workspace

Find the project and import it.
















Try and compile. You should see an error as the StemWin libraries are not in the repository.



Find the STM32CubeMX repository with the StemWin files. You need to copy the Lib directory over to your TFT project. You need only the 2 files shown below. They need to be renamed so that they have lib infront of the name. You may need to go File – Refresh in order to see them in you System Workbench.




















Look at the StemWin pdf under the repositories documentation directory and create a screen showing “ECET260 – Lab 4” in a large font centered horizontally on the screen and your name in a smaller font below it. Choose an suitable background and font color to make the text readable.



Upload a picture of your TFT screen to the LAB4 D2L dropbox by the start of lab week 5.
